reviews: Very charming hostel in the midst of Montmartre, at the foot of Sacre Cœur. The personnel speak French as well as English and are very helpful. There are both single rooms and dormitory and a small kitchen if you want to cook. A special secret is the outside terrasse on the first floor for both a calm breakfast and for meeting other guests in the evening!

I was happy staying at this hostel untill i realised that they had taken extra money from my account for no reason. I think that they are scammers everyone beware. I had paid my reservation and paod for my stay.

I thoroughly enjoyed my stay at the hostel, and the staff were very friendly and welcoming. It is also situated in a nice place close to shops and public transport. Breakfast is also served with variety.

The perfect location to start exploring Paris, in the cosy Montmartre neighborough surrounded by art galleries, shops, restaurants, supermarkets and bars and very close to the subway M2, the hostel itself is very clean and reasonably prices, all the rooms have ensuite bathroom there's also a terrace with view of the Sacre Coeur church, staff very friendly and professional, definitely I would highly recommend!

We booked a one night stay after lots of researching the area and it did not disappoint. Was easy to find and we were greeted by a lovely woman on reception. The whole place was spotless, even the shared kitchen. We had a private room on the third floor and the view was of the Parisian streets which was perfect.
Is right next to two supermarkets which we grabbed food from and 2 minutes from the sacrer couer.
The stairs are quite narrow and steep but beautiful exposed brick.
Would recommend this place for all

Very conveniently located, stones throw away from a few metro stations supermarkets and pharmacies, and in a hipster neighbourhood. Super friendly and helpful staff who speak good English. Cosy rooms and well equipped kitchen. Will highly recommend

I slept on a girls only room and it was good. This was my first time in a hostel and the experience was perfect! Clean hostel nearby sacre coeur. The metrostation anvers is 2min walk. And the terrace is amazing! Low budget, safe and fine stay.

Incredible location right at the foot of the butte de Montmartre. The little terrace on the 1st floor looks right up onto the Sacré Coeur. Le Village had very clean and warm rooms, a welcoming lobby and tables to sit at, and a really beautiful porch that I imagine is pretty sweet during the summertime. The guests were all very respectful and there were a range of groups of friends, solo travelers, and families (I didn't see any small children). Not a party hostel per se, but a great place to relax and mingle with other travelers.

Wake up to views of sacre cour, close to metro, or 15 min walk to Gare du Nord. Awesome staff v friendly, clean room and affordable (for paris). Our twin room had just enough space for us to unfurl after a day of walking, and the outdoor area was a great spot to have dinner and get tips from fellow travellers.

Metro nearby, adorable neighborhood to wander around in, clean, quiet, hot water, 15 min walk from train station that connects you to airport. Grocery less than a minute walk away, plenty of cafes, etc. around. Neighborhood felt safe. Wifi worked well in lobby & room. Was really only there to sleep.

No real complaints, but hated how small the shower was....would totally stay again.

I had a reservation at Le Village from Sept 12-15, 2019, but had to leave earlier because of bed bugs! The place was far from clean! The worst part of it all, I’ve emailed their customer service and I’ve not heard anything back! Apparently, one of the people in the room have mentioned that they might have seen a bed bug in the room, and instead of doing anything about it such as getting the people in the room out, they let it be and ignored it. The next day, I woke up with bed bug bites all over me! Upon examining the room, there were blood stains on the walls and even on the sheets, which just shows how this can’t be the first time this had been brought up! I checked out earlier, but since I’ve paid for the 3 nights, the reception couldn’t even help me get my money back! Per the staff at the desk, “the manager is analyzing the situation.” Apparently, according to the staff, their manager even said to continue renting out the room, but she made the decision to close it for now. This is very concerning as bed bugs travel quickly if not taken care of earlier! I had to find another accommodation last minute, disinfect all of my belongings, and even had to go to a pharmacy for medications, instead of exploring Paris as planned. I’ve emailed the manager after the event and I’ve emailed their customer representative rep, and I still have not received anything back yet! This is literally the worst!

Really comfortable, good value, and well located. I stayed in a private room, and it was as good as any hotel room I’ve stayed in, with quite a spacious en suite (and decent shower). The staff were all friendly and very helpful. There’s also a lounge area, kitchen, and terrace, so plenty of opportunities to meet others whilst there. Paris itself is great, and the hostel was very close to the metro and also many shops, cafes, and bars in montmarte itself.

I stayed for 3 days in this hostel, great location, close to everything especially Montmartre area and the cathedral as well as Pigalle district...
On other hand, the cleanliness of the place make me speechless, the shower and WC remained cleaned anytime I use them...
A comfy bed and pillow, staff are extremely friendly and nice, especially the hostel front office team and the hostel manager Mrs Iris gave me a very good recommendation how to spend my day....
I definitely recommend this place...see you soon

Great place in Montmartre for a stay in Paris. Nice and spacious double bedrooms. Little supermarket just opposite.The location is just unbeatable. Easily accessable metro station just round the corner.There is secure underground parking about 400 metres away which was fantastic as our stay was a stopover and we could leave our other stuff in the car.

We stayed in a private double room with private en-suite in room. The room was light and clean with detailed wooden roof I adored. We have two windows opening out onto the street with a lovely view of the adjacent Parisian building. We opted out of the 6euro daily breakfast, but often there were left over croissants and baguettes you could help yourself to. The staff were very welcoming and knowledgeable, and always someone at the counter. Our stay was comfortable and pleasant, on the 3rd floor it was nice and quiet. The location is perfect for cafes, restaurants, two great supermarkets and all the souvenirs you could want, all within seconds of stepping out of the hostel. Would highly recommend this hostel.

We have been staying in Le Village Hostel at the foot of Montmartre for many years. It is a great location close to Metro and Bus stops and a short walk,Funicular ride or Bus 30 to the top of Montmatre and Sacre Coeur. The accommodation is more than what you may consider to be hostel standard. We are well into our 60's and find it totally comfortable and accessible. There is a kitchen facility to prepare your own meals but to be honest we eat out in one of the many bars and restaurants in the area.

If you are staying in Paris and want reasonably priced accommodation with access by public transport to the whole of Paris or just somewhere to dander around soaking up the Parisian atmosphere I would highly recommend Le Village.

The staff is always extremely helpful and ready to serve. They keep the place impeccably clean and it's a perfect location to easily access Montmartre, Sacre Coeur, and the Anvers Metro station is just a block away which makes it so easy to access any sight in Paris that you want to visit! Plus I always meet the nicest guests from all over the world in this friendly environment. I especially like it that you can prepare your own meals in their kitchen, and there are 2 grocery stores right nearby to find the type of food you want to prepare!

One of the best hostels I stayed. It was vary comfortable and the location was amazing, every night I enjoyed to read my book watching the Sacre Cœur. If my holiday in Paris was amazing, one of the reason was this hostel

I am not used to staying at hostels but I got stuck due to short notice and the date coincided with the fashion week. When I went to bed, I started getting insects bites, at first I thought they were mosquitoes but they just wouldn’t stop, I started looking in the bed and then I saw it. Bed bugs! At 2 am, i left my bed, collected my bag and stayed at the lobby until the morning the I left for my other hotel. The room was 103 and the bed was the upper bed right in front of the door.

Stayed in a double room for 3 nights while visiting Paris. Check in is strictly at 3pm but we arrived at 11am and were allowed to store our bags and use the common rooms!
Once we got into our room we were very impressed - the room was spacious, had AC and our our private bathroom with a shower. The room was very clean! Came with basic furniture (bed nightstand, lamp, small desk/stool) but was everything that was needed. We were also pleasantly surprised that we were provided towels (I think this is maybe just for the private rooms as there was a sign in the lobby about renting towels?)There is a supermarket and plenty of little shops directly across the road.
The desk is staffed 24/7 and they were very helpful with the checkin/checkout process (checked out at 530am with no problem!)

This was our first experience of a hostel as a family (2 daughters aged 9 and 7), and Le Village was perfect for our needs. It was friendly and safe, and in a great neighbourhood - it is literally at the bottom of the steps to the Sacre Coeur, with a supermarket and pharmacy over the road, and plenty of shops and restaurants around. Breakfast was great, and we could use the kitchen to make our own food which was handy. The room was basic but spotless, and our daughters loved us all sleeping in bunk beds 😀. And thank goodness it had aircon, as Paris was in the midst of a 40+'c heatwave during our visit. All in all we had a great stay, and would recommend to those looking for clean and safe, but basic, accomodation.

Such a beautiful hostel, in a gorgeous area. A stunning terrace with tables and a hammock where you can see the top of Sacre Cœur from.

The rooms were clean with everything we needed, towels, soap, shampoo, as well as free coffee and tea which was refreshed every day.

There is also a kitchen which guests are free to use. There’s a microwave, fridge, blender, kettle, stove, and oven. Some foods are left out for people to use as they want, and there’s a supermarket literally next door where you can buy ingredients if you want to cook.

The people working here were super friendly - our train was massively delayed so we ended up arriving at about 2am and we were worried we wouldn’t be able to check in that late but we called ahead and there was someone there to greet us.

An absolute hidden gem - I cannot recommend this highly enough!

After spending time in regular budget hostels this place was like a genuine heaven; the double room we stayed in had not only an en-suite bathroom and air conditioning (probably the best bit) but a daily cleaning service! Felt much more like a hotel than a hostel, and an expensive one at that.
Excellent kitchen facilities (microwave, hob, big fridge, kettles, even a blender!) and the decor in the lobby is beautiful. Has a little terrace with couches and a hammock which is lovely to eat on in the evenings.
Location is really gorgeous; you can see the sacre cœur from the terrace and the streets are full of fabric shops. Right next to a supermarket and 5-10 min walk from the ‘barbés-rochechouart’ metro stop. You definitely need to pay for transport to visit the classic tourist sites, but that’s true of anywhere.
Overall a lovely experience, still in disbelief that it was our least expensive stay with the facilities and environment being far superior to other hostels we’ve stayed in!

Stayed with my friend in a shared all female room. It was our first hostel visit all alone ever and we couldn’t have wished for a better place! The staff was incredibly kind and caring. Rooms were clean and quiet. Nice location and a really nice lobby downstairs with a modern kitchen and cozy places to sit.

I don’t normally write negative reviews and i has to on this place. This was my second hostel experience and I hated it. My friend and I got paired with two males and one of the males was doing some sexually inappropriate things and trying to take pictures of my friend. When we told the staff we wanted to move, they wouldn’t let us.
The breakfast was not good either. I would of rather used my money to pay for breakfast in Paris. They also say you have to pay for WiFi and that’s just dumb!

The location of this hostel is perfect. Lovely decor, close to the city central. The whole place was spotlessly clean and it was nice having a bathroom in our room. As a solo traveller I loved the social atmosphere of this hotel so much, I will definitely come back to this hostel next time! Highly recommended!

This very good HOSTEL,Very Nice location close from Wonderful Sacre KER,very good Room,very Clean,very Cozy,very comfy,very close AMAIZING Franprix Magazine,good Lounge,THANK YOU VERY MATCH LA VILLAGE HOSTEL,VERY GRATITUDE FOR YOU!!!

I booked a private room in this hostel for three nights, and had to leave after one. The room smelled so strongly of mould, I was afraid to stay there because of my health. The room was also reverberating with the sound of the music at the pub nearby, so loudly at 2am that I could have sung along. It was also freezing, due to the single glazed windows and cheap bedding. My towels had hairs on them that were clearly not mine, and the floor was dirty. The whole place was just disgusting, as was their attitude when I tried to ask for a refund. I couldn't contact anyone, through any channel, and so I ended up paying for 3 nights. Thank goodness it was only cheap but I will never again stay there and I recommend anyone else go somewhere (anywhere!!) else besides this disgrace of a hostel.

Oh, it also lied on its room description. Said I had a city view when I had a view of the street outside, and said they provided ear plugs when they didn't. Also the photos are overly photoshopped. It doesn't look that nice. It's way more dingy than that...

BEWARE..this Hostel won't let you book more than 8 people. I am a parent trying to book a group of 12. I saw that there was rooms on the website but they make me send a group booking online. Then they contact you in 48 hours!
By then the rooms were not available. My friend booked the 3 rooms online no problem and they cancelled his reservation because I did not go through the group booker. Then the group booker emailed that the rooms are not available! But the rooms are still available on the website. I called the manager to inquire about the problem and she let me know that she didn't want our group at her hostel because I was trying to book the room without using the group booker. This seems to be the experience at the Hip Hop Hostels in general. Probably okay if you are only a few people, but avoid if you have a group or have to deal with management for any reason. They are inflexible and very rude.

Location was amazing, staff were friendly, everything was always clean (including the bathroom :)) and my favourite part was the view - Sacre-Coeur looked beautiful from my dorm!!!!!! It could've been even better if lockers were bigger ;)

One of the best hostels i have ever stayed in.
The staff at the reception was super patient and very very helpful. They felt like family.
The kitchen is open 24hrs, with tea sachets and bread - jam available anytime for those late night bites.
Its very very clean.
Its pretty well located- just minutes frm the metro lines, opp a super market and close to bars as well.
They organise well priced shuttles to the airport.
One of receptionists even came to knock at my door as a wakeup call bfr my flight :)
They had lovely wine n cheese on thursday evngs :)
They lockers at no cost. Carry a padlock. Else they have other coded lockers in the common section as well :)

Downside (very minor):
A slightly noisyish bar which can annoy others. Didnt bother me.They offer earplugs.
The soap in a sharing private bathroom should ideally be the pump bottles and not a soap bar.

All in all, a definite recommend. Id stay here again.

I've travelled many hostels all around the globe, and this one was astonishingly clean. Breakfast could be a bit more sometimes, maybe some more activities for on-stayers, but I was more than happy. And it was very comfy. One even doesn't have to clean one's own dishes ^^

I was in Paris last minute for one night only, so booked a hostel and this one was in a great location and cheap.
Staff were really friendly, and helpful. My only issue was, I was out LATE and enjoying the nightlife. I guess everyone else in my room had an early night, before 8am someone got up and opened the curtains and windows. Not great for sleep. Then later a girl was in the bathroom doing good knows what for 90mins. That's not the fault of the hostel though, it's the ignorance of my room-mates!

I was there with my friends and we stayed in a private room for four. It was cozy and lovely. Lovely staff too!
We loved that it was close to the Sacre Coeur. The kitchen was pretty well equipped too.

Room and bathroom were clean. Got noisy on Saturday night. Great location. Friendly staff. Room for 3 had a bunk bed and twin. Bathroom was small but clean. Extra fee for towels so we took our own. Would stay there again

Me and my friend stayed in the hostel overnight and we could not have been happier. We arrived 3 hours before check-in was possible and the staff (Norman) kindly asked if we wanted to leave our bags all day. The location is brilliant, seconds away from the Sacré Coeur, it is surrounded by restaurants, shops and bars and minutes away from Anvers metro station. For this price (65 Euros/night for 2 people), I have stayed in MANY places in Paris and they were usually quite dodgy! Here, the staff (a lovely girl from Madrid and a French guy with a cool hair cut :) were welcoming and fun, always polite (they probably aren't all Parisians to be fair! haha), the rooms are perfectly clean and have everything you need. Our night was mostly quiet but they even provide ear plugs at reception. The desk is manned all night too so there really is everything you could need. We didn't use the kitchen but that also looked really clean and well equipped when we whizzed through. I really could not recommend this place any more! They were even able to book a Airport Shuttle for us... Bravo à toute l'équipe! ;-)

Spent 3 nights here in September (solo traveler), and was very pleased with the accommodations. Rooms + bathrooms were kept in good, clean condition and seemed to be cleaned daily. The kitchen was well stocked and all of the concierges were quite nice. The beautiful deck is also a nice touch. All in all had a nice stay here, and would recommend it to anyone looking for a simple, clean and well-located hostel in Paris.

This hostel hits more right notes than just about any other I’ve ever been to. It’s right in the middle of an up and coming area, in a world class city, with value stores and bars right next to it, and personalized amenities😬 they even have showers in every room! The facilities in the lobby are small since the area itself is small, but it’s made up for by the cozy feel. I also felt it was a great value for the money!

The hostel is placed in 10/10 location - next to train station, opposite supermarket , right next to pup , 2 minute walk to metro, 5 minute walk to a street full of restaurants and right next to Montmartre.

The hostel it self quite standard, access to the privet terrace, really friendly service and small and limiting kitchen facilities.

Overall I would def stay again and recommend.

We stayed for three nights in a double room with private bathroom and paid 90€/night. We know it's Paris and this is a hostel, it was not our first time, but the only thing in the room and the bathroom which looked like the photos on the website was the violet wall. Nothing else. Furniture and decoration were completely different or just not available. The room was so tiny we had to walk over our handluggage (HANDLUGGAGE!) to go to the bathroom. The window and the door were like not existing as well: you hear everything. They have a pub on the corner and it was very noisy up to us on the 4th floor. They also don't close properly, so the room was cold and a bit windy during the whole night. The tiniest lift I've ever seen has sometimes light, sometimes a bit of it and sometimes it's dark at all. And yeah, sometimes it just doesn't work at all.
The only nice thing here is the friendly staff, but come on: 90€/night for that? Never again.

There are so many great things about Le Village Hostel Montmartre that I cannot write a short review. Please take the time to read the entire review as I think it will be helpful.
Location!
1] Short walk (less than 5 minutes) from the Metro, 2] a small bar next door, 3] the next door to that is a fully stocked grocery store with a spectacular salad bar with the latest of sneeze guards, 4] a three minute walk to a laundromat that is reasonably priced, and 5] a short walk (maybe 10 minutes) to a major city hospital and myriad pharmacies. Yes, I was very sick while I was in Paris - bummer. I will return and stay at Le Village.
The Staff!
The welcome I received and the explanation of the entire complex were wonderful. It made me feel like they really wanted me there. I met five reception people (including the manager) and several cleaning staff and they all were pleasant and genuinely wanted to help me with any questions, problems, or personal needs. Praise to them all.
The Facility!
Yes, it is an older building, but very nice and has an elevator if needed. The kitchen has clearly been upgraded recently as the cabinets and appliances were all quite new and easy to keep clean AND unlike other hostels, the kitchen is open 24 hours a day. The patio is a rooftop area that invites camaraderie among guests. It does close between 10:00 and 11:00 p.m. so as not to disturb guests whose rooms are nearby.
Some things to consider!
1]Bar soap and shampoo are supplied free of charge.
2]Bath towels are available for rent at 2.5€ per towel.
3]Printing of tickets purchased on line and other printing needs are available free of charge.
4]Thursday evening presented a free wine & cheese tasting.
5]Airport transportation is easy by bus or Metro, but better yet, at the door drop off and pick up can be arranged.
6l]Before purchasing condiments and other food items, check the “free food” left behind by others. You could eat your whole stay at the hostel without spending any money if you were to be creative and not particular.
7]The bar next door plays moderately loud music until it closes after midnight. It was not loud enough to disturb me, but if little noises keep you from sleeping bring ear plugs.

Really nice rooms, hotel standard bathrooms, air con and individual plugs and lights. Really friendly staff go above and beyond. Giod wifi and nice pub next door. Perfect for travelling, would definitely stay again if back in Paris. Can't recommend enough!

Stayed there for three nights. The atmosphere was really good, nothing to complain about during our stay. The staff was friendly, short walking distance from the city central and the neighbourhood is cosy and nice. Would recommend for travellers on a budget.

I stayed here just one night but found it to be quite good. The colorful terrace area with glimpses of Sacre Coeur is the highlight. Rooms were basic but comfortable and a kitchen area is available. An affiliated backpackers pub is next door, which is convenient but can get loud. Having a 24 hour front desk is helpful. Gard du Nord station is a walkable distance and there are several nearby metro stops. The surrounding neighborhood has many cafes and grocery options. I've stayed both here and at the other nearby Hiphostel property, Vintage, and I might choose this one as my favorite just because of the pleasant terrace area.

I cannot fault the staff at this hostel, they are friendly, helpful and go out their way to make sure you are ok. However, the hostel is situated next do a pub and has single glazing windows - this means you can hear music, laughing, conversations etc until the pub closes. This makes it almost impossible to sleep. It was so bad we ended up staying at a friends apartment in Paris so we could sleep. We thought it would just be noisy on the Saturday but every day was loud. I would advise asking to be at the back of the hostel or bite the bullet and spend some extra dollar. The transport links are great from the hostel, however it is in a dodgy area so be careful and don't walk around by yourself.

The hostel is mostly really great. The kitchen is well equipped, and everything is well managed and clean. You can buy some nessecities from the front desk but its better to bring your own. There's a shop next door food which is really useful.

The main problem we encountered was the bar next door plays loud music until quite late most night but earplugs solved that fine.

There's a guitar and ukulele in the reception which you can borrow which was a cool perk as well.

This hostel was our first stop on a 3 week European adventure and was one of my favorite places we stayed (we did a mix of hostels and Airbnb’s). The staff were very friendly and let us arrive early and leave our bags with them before our rooms were ready. We booked a 4 bed mixed dorm but ended up having the whole room to ourselves for the duration of our trip so we basically got a private room for the dorm price (which was amazing!). Air conditioning was not on at first so it was slightly musty, but after an afternoon that went away. Comfortable beds and we appreciated the private bathroom and secure entrances. Very close to multiple metro line stops so it’s super easy to get around Paris. I would recommend getting the multi-day tourist pass that gives you unlimited metro and buss rides. Great restaurants near by and a very cool pub next door to have a drink. I would recommend going across the street to the market and getting a chocolate croissant or two for breakfast for a cheap and quick bite to eat to start your day.

Our room had a window from which we could see the Sacre Coeur, absolutely beautiful day and night. Clean room, bathroom as well as common places. Good breakfast. Friendly staff, multi-language. Location is dreamy!! Loved the neighbourhood, maybe insecure at night, but still beautiful and confortable since the metro is near the hostel. Nothing to complaint about, truly. Great experience!

I stayed at Le Village for 3 nights in a mixed dorm. The beds were comfy, sheet, blanket and pillow provided. Good A/C and room was kept very clean. Small lockers available. No hot water one day but that was the only issue. I didn’t use the kitchen but it looked pretty well equipped. Staff were very friendly and helpful. It’s a little ways out from the city centre but Anvers station is a 2 minute walk so it’s super quick getting to the action. I’d stay again.

very closed to metro station and some interesting attractions. two supermarkets seel good varieties and cheap at each side of the hostel. friendly and helpful staff. well equipped kitchenette although a bit small but good enough

We had a great stay here. Clean and has a well equipped kitchen, the beds are a little small though. The terrace was a very nice place to hang out as well. Staff is very helpfull, even though check in was delayed, we were still allowed to use the showers. Would definitely stay here again

Best location, nice and clean, and accessible to metro etc. Had the best stay at this hostel and really recommend it as I went there with my husband for our honeymoon. One of the restaurants downstairs was one of our favourites, and really awesome for meeting new people from around the world.

Stayed at this hostel for a few days with a friend this past weekend. The beds were soft, the room was clean, and the staff was friendly; however, we weren’t aware beforehand that it is attached to a loud pub or club. The room was very, very loud. It wasn’t a big deal for us because neither of us ever struggle to sleep but it’s something to be aware of. Also, there was a mix-up at check in where they overbooked our room by one person and almost kicked my friend out of the room. The staff handled it quite well and upgraded one of the other girls so we could stay in the room but my friend had to remake her bed which was a little annoying but at least we had a place to stay.

The hostel is located under a night club so don't expect a good nights sleep. Also the showers didny work properly, no water pressure and turned off every few seconds. The Wi-Fi didn't work at all. All that and the price isnt cheap either. Really not impressed.

The hostel its near The sacre coeur. Just spent some hours there and it was fine but I felt that could be better If they care more about the conditions of the dorms. Didnt use but the kitchen looks great.

I stayed here by myself Sept. 18-21 in a 4 all female room. We were on the 4th floor and there also was an elevator. My room also had a bathroom, although the shower was really small. The room had one window with an excellent view of rhe Sacre Coer! The town Montmartre is a cute town that ia close to a lot of bakeries and stores. There are 2 metro stops that are close to the hostel too, they are about a block away. The staff is super nice amd friendly! They have a nice common area and a kitchen with a pretty big fridge.
I loved this place and would definitely stay again and recommend!

Stayed here for two nights 29th - 31st August. Room 405 was very clean and bed was comfortable. Didn't have a great sleep as there was noise from pub next door and traffic but i was only there two nights so wasn't a big issue. Breakfast was a wee bit pricey at 6 euros but was tasty. Overall I enjoyed my stay and would definitely go back and recommend to friends and family.

The toilet and bathroom are tiny and have no ventilation system so they smell terrible.

The beds are really squeaky. The mattress was uncomfortable. In their photos, they show the beds pre-made ready for guests however they are not. They provided two flat sheets which were stained and a blanket which they might not be replacing between guests.

No bar to socialise.Breakfast not included. The oven wasn't functional in the kitchen. It go pretty cold at night without a duvet.

One of the receptionist was rude, however the others were nice and helpful.

The terrace was a nice place to socialise however it got pretty loud at night when people were trying to sleep.

Very friendly staff, clean enough, cheap, very convenient location, good night's sleep.

No towels provided in dormitory (Only negative)

Nice cheap bar next door, plenty of places to get dinner and breakfast nearby.

I stayed in a private double room for 3 nights (room 302). It was a corner bedroom so I had two windows. The private bathroom was small but clean. The bed mattress was firm and very comfortable - I slept well. There were a couple of available electrical outlets that I used to charge my devices at night. Wifi is free, but not quite fast enough if you're planning to use it to upload a lot of photos. The air conditioner was much appreciated!

There is a bar next door if you're feeling social at night, and you're just a couple blocks from some incredible restaurants. The staff was very friendly and helpful. I would highly recommend it if you plan on staying in the area.

I was welcomed by a very friendly guy (who's name I cannot remember) and was offered cheese and wine and popcorn. This is such a nice welcoming. very appreciative!

I stayed in a private room on the first floor. The room was clean, bigger than I expected, nice bed and shower.

Location is great!!! You are a minuets away from the Montmartre and so many local restaurants, bars and patisseries.

The hostel is above a bar so it does gets a bit noisy until 1am or so on the weekend but it did not bother me at all.

I highly recommend this great place! A gem in Paris.

The 24 hour reception was super useful, staff are really friendly and eager to offer advice. The area surrounding is nicer on the historic side, the immediate area around felt safe and touristy even coming in late. The rooms were standard, clean, and with lockers which were useful.

It's location cannot be better. Right in Montmartre, nearby cool bars, and beautiful sights. Also, very near the subway, so you can get essentially anywhere in no time.
The hostel in itself does it's job. The bathroom is pretty good, and beds are ok. My bed in particular didn't have a power slot, so it was kind an issue.
It has a beautiful terrace perfect for chilling during the day, and it's next door to an awesome bar for the night.
Michael, the receptionist, is the best recepcionist you can ask for. Super cool guy who will do anything he can to help out and make your stay great.

Absolutely lovely stay at Le Village Hostel. We booked a private double room which was beautifully decorated, clean and included an en-suite with shower. Bed was modern, firm and very comfortable.
Fantastic location.
Norman and the rest of the staff were very welcoming, helpful and friendly. We requested an extra pillow and it was sorted immediately. Having stayed at some less than nice hotels in Paris we're delighted to find this place and will make it our first choice for accommodation in Paris!

I stayed in a 4 bedroom female dorm and was quite pleased with the quietness of the hostel. Laid back with a nice balcony to sit and have a chat to fellow travellers. Good location in the trendy area of Montmarte with lots of cute cafes and award-winning bakeries near by. Easy access to the train and main tourist spots. Overall a good place to stay.

Clean hostel in easy access to Gare du Nord, metro and Sacre Coeur. Helpful, multilingual staff, full kitchen access and supermarket 2 doors down. Very cute terrace, good for a drink or eating or a break from the busy streets. Building lift saves the pain of lifting luggage up stairs.

For sure it was one of the best hostels that I've ever been. The room was nice, the staff really kind and the rooftop was amazing to drink some wine and chat. The area is really nice as well, with lovely places to go. I truly recommend.

The hostel is located near Gare du Nord in fairly rough area of Paris.

It's quite cramped in the hostel given its location in the city. This is not a critique of the hostel but an observation itself.

The hostel was clean, however the common room was quite cramped.

Complimentary lockers require your own padlocks and the complimentary lockers are pay to use.

The hostel bar is very expensive and filled with locals which makes it very difficult for non French speaking guests.

The hostel charges an arm and a leg for drinks stocked in the reception and breakfast is expensive.

The staff was a mixed bag for me, Michael and Albert were very friendly and nice to talk too but the management seemed unreasonable. I paid upfront for 5 days but due to unforseen circumstances required to leave a day early, despite telling them at the heart start of my stay of this change I was refused a refund.

It's a shame as this was an okay hostel on its own but it was sullied by a few small things that really should not be happening.

I like this Hostel, nearby to the train stations, really close to Montmartre. The staff is really nice and Friendly, they speak several languages, I liked that they have an "Only Girls" bump beds and room, with private bathroom. Breakfast is Ok for 6 Euros (you get cereal, Oj and a Croissant + Coffe/Tea). I would recommend it to my friend and will stay there again. On the streets you might get harassed but that happened in all Paris. not only nearby the Hostel.

Not the worst place I have stayed in but I was not impressed. The toilet smelled pretty bad like piss, and there weren't enough keys for the room I stayed in so we had to return them to the front desk when we left the hostel so that other people staying in the room could use it to enter the room. Don't get the breakfast: it is 6.50 and if you book it online even though you haven't paid yet they will refuse to let you cancel it. Stale bread, watered down orange drink, and croissants . . . just don't. It is a really noisy area with the bar down below. A lot of street harassment goes on in the area so women watch out. On the plus side it is close to Sacre Couer which is beautiful.

This hostel is very well located near to public transit and tourism sites. Our room was extremely nice - spacious, well-maintained, clean, and attractive. Michael helped us and he was very polite and helpful. Diogo also helped us and the same could be said there. The employees really made this hostel stand out. The kitchen was good and there were many resources in the hostel, like cards you could take with directions to spots of interest. The terrace is a nice touch. During week nights, it was nice and quiet. Our first night there was a Saturday and the noise from the bar below made it difficult to sleep - our room was right above it. We expected this to be noisy especially on a weekend, but actually I thought the music was overly loud and could not be drowned up by ear plugs, so it woke me up a couple times as I was trying to sleep (shortly before midnight, so it's no problem if you're out late). All said, it was a good experience and I would definitely stay here again.

This is the first time I sleep in a dorm, and I will do it again. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable. The breakfast was adequate. Free WIFI. All this at the right price. The bar is located underneath the property but you get a beer if you come from the hostel.

The location is too far from attractions. Our room wasn't clean and a lot of things were dated and needing attention. I was bitten by bed bugs in one of the private rooms on our first night, however they moved us and we appreciated it a lot. we will not be staying here again though.

Claire at the front desk (who has great style and taste) was very friendly, welcoming and helpful. She upgraded our stay to a private room because one was available at no additional charge. The hostel was clean, well kept, quiet and lovely! Our stay was fantastic.

We chose the venue due to good TripAdvisor rating. We spent 3 days with my wife at a double bedroom and 3 days extended with my sister and her boyfriend in a 4 bunkbed room. Breakfast is poor. Undrinkable orange juice, generally small assortment of food. Small bedrooms, small bathrooms. paper thin walls - you can hear everything. Cleaning was also questionable. Thin blankets. Staff was very kind though.

The good thing about this hostel is its location..Just next to Sacre Coeur. Its literally at the foot steps of it.. Hostel is clean. Also offers fresh Linen/Towel for use. Hostel is very clean. I stayed in 4 Bed ensuite..washrooms/toilets were nice and clean.

Dorm is not that big and lockers are small. Metro Station is just couple of minutes away and super market is right across. Wifi is great!!

Staff is friendly and will help you with all the information.

It is a nice hostel for the price it comes.

Great location just in front of the sacré coeur, staff couldn't have been more friendly or helpful and the hostel was very clean and comfortable. Two minutes walk from the metro so easy to get around everywhere. Me and my partner stayed in a private double room with our own bathroom and it was perfect. Obviously because it's primarily a youth hostel and beside a bar it can be noisy at night but it usually quieted down not long after midnight. The hostel also has a nice private terrace on the first floor where you can sit in the sun. It was about 40 euro each for us each night which is great for Paris and if the prices do not increase I would definitely stay here again and recommend it to my friends.

My stay at Le Village Hostel was an awesome experience, i didnt expect the rooms to be so nice or the beds so comfy, but they were. Stayed on the first floor overlooking the street and the patio. The reception desk personnel, claire, micheal, voorman and kat were on point with their service. They all spoke english very well which was great cause my french sucked. They were extremely helpful in getting me around to different locals around paris. I would definitely recommend this place to stay in. Be sure to book in advance cause they do fill up. Wen u go, tell them RJ sent u, my logo is on the cooler next to their desk.

Had such a great stay here! The staff are lovely people. Also the Sacre Ceour is close by if you feel like going for a morning run. The location is ideal as it is near a metro stop. Kitchen is fully equipped and wifi working very well. I will definitely stay here again the next time I visit! Great value for money!

This has by far been the best hostel I have stayed at during my European travels. I loved the staff and the facilities. I stayed in a four bed, to which was graciously upgraded. The others staying there were so respectful and one of my roommates was awesome (one snored really loudly but oh well). The kitchen was well kept, and they do offer breakfast. The terrace is gorgeous! Definitely go out there! The place is super accessible too! The only downside is that the stairs are super steep, but there is a elevator (tiny but functional) to compensate, also it is a bit more expensive than other hostels I have stayed in, but worth it! Thanks for a great stay!

Had a lovely stay at the hostel. Michael and the rest of the staff made our stay easy and friendly. Our room was simple but peaceful with a Parisian street view. Monmart is just round the corner, there is a subway station within two minutes walk and a friendly bar next door that stays open late. I will stay there again.

I just staid there for some nights and it was wonderful, to star the team working there is awesome, when I arrive and they found out that I was speaking Spanish they instantly start to speak to, it was a nice surprise! The rooms are really good and warm, which was great because of the freezing weather, they have a nice an big terraza and also a great kitchen if you want to cook for yourself. The location couldn't be better, just a couple of block away from the Sacré-coeur and also a metro line so it's perfect. The only thing that I didn't liked is that the smell from the bathrooms was a little bit disgusting, they should take care of it but the rest was wonderful, definitely coming back!

This was the best hostel I've ever stayed at! It has everything you could wish for in a cheap hostel; clean rooms, full kitchen, great location, and awesome environment. It is less than a ten minute walk to the metro and is close to the Sacre Coeur and great restaurants/shops. The staff was super friendly and helpful. I will definitely return!!!

Victoria at the front desk had great recommendations of things to do, places to eat, shops, etc. in Paris. In fact, the entire front desk staff was friendly, helpful-- every interaction was positive. Free shots and beer at a bar they give you a coupon at. This is not only one of the best boutique hostels, but hostels in general-- the atmosphere is much more preferable to me than, for example, St. Christopher's (and the hot water doesn't run out nearly as fast as it does at the St. Christopher's Gare du Nord). The location is impeccable-- walkable to Anvers and a few other metros, in one of the greatest neighborhoods Paris (and next to Pigalle, which has alot of clubs and seedy joints [it's a cool neighborhood to check out at least once]). I'll stay here again next time I come through if I need a quick room. I was really pleased with my experience and will recommend it to all of my backpacking buddies, along with any of there other hostels.

Word of advice-- book directly from their website for better rates and (I believe) the free shots/ beer. This is good advice with hostels in general.

It all depends on our experiences obviously. Mine wasn't that good. I have no complains about the hostel, as it was good, staff very friendly too.
But walking around the area suddenly a couple of guys went to me offering a gift with no cost and then after another 3 came asking for at least 20 euro. I didn't know exactly how to react but I gave them just in case something bad happen.
About the hostel I have nothing to say, it is good. This happened in 2013 but on the website the option is not avaliable. Sorry about that.

As an experienced hostel traveler, I know that the quality of the hostel you've chosen can influence the overall experience of your city-trip. And I can conclude that I have had a WONDERFUL time at Le Village Hostel! The rooms are clean, the WiFi is perfect but most of all, the staff is truly friendly and helpful. Diogo, Norman, Katya, Claire and especially Justine, merci beaucoup. Au revoir!

This was my fourth time in the City of Light, and, francly, I love staying in this hostel. l like the quartier, it's super easy tout reach using the metro, and the place has a good atmosphere. Staff is friendly and helpfull and the rooms are kept clean. Everything is close, if you want to go out or to the supemarket, and the common room is very good, if you want to meet other travellers.
I'm sure to make another reservation, hopefully soon!

Stayed here for 3 nights in January on a solo trip. The staff is very friendly, the rooms are clean and Metro is near by. Great atmosphere. Was very easy to meet people. Only downside was the breakfast. It was much to simple and not worth the extra price. Other than that I highly recommend staying here.

Helpful staff, good security, tons of information to get around the city, coupons for a bar just down the street, within walking distance of Moulin Rouge (GO!), comfy beds and clean bathrooms. Also a grocery store across the street and lovely outdoor patio to hang out in the hostel. Highly recommended!

Great hostel in a cool part of Paris. Near the metro and some great restaurants. I wouldn't wander the neighborhood alone at night, but with a companion it's perfectly safe. Beds are comfortable, shower and toilets are in the room. Can't beat it for the price.

The staff was incredible. Really helped me book a train ticket I needed the next day to Barcelona. And the bathroom!! I really didn't expect such a nice, clean and spacious one. Location of the hostel is great. They have a bar next to it too. You get a free welcome shot if you stay in the hostel.

The people behind the counter are very helpful. The rooms and the facility are fantastic . I recommend the stay to couples and solo travellers. If you need help moving around don't forget to ask the staff they will go over the top to help.

This hostel is really clean and the location is awesome you can walk to the Anver train station (Get a Mobilis pass) and move from there to wherever you want. There is also a bar right next to the hostel which is nice too. Also you can go to Sacre Cour and have a beautiful dinner. There is a laundry close by and also fast food. The people from the front desk are really kind.
Bad side is that the street that goes to the Station have a lot of people trying to sell stuff, for your own good ignore all voices. Also the breakfast was extremely basic, that can be improved.

5 nights in a four bed female room.

One outlet in our four female bed room was broken. There were only three outlets, so we had only two available for four people, which was inconvenient. The breaker for our room tripped for a couple of hours we could not use it, either. Our room people asked the reception to fix it twice and then they did.

One personal locker was broken out of four, I could not use it because three of them were already in use.

1/5 of the shower water was leaking.

The kitchen was convenient for cooking on my own. They provided knives, pans, bowls and several strong cookers.

The lounge, our room and bath rooms were very clean.

Wifi was strong and free of charge.

Well located, you can get to Gare de l'Est from the nearest station Anvers 15 mins by metro.
Only 25 mins by train to Marais.

The neighborhood I felt was safe, a lot of wholesale stores for cloth along the streets. It was just a little dirty all around the streets.

For the location and wrong information and insufficient service by reception, I will not come again, but it was very cheap anyway, thank you...

My friend and I stayed here for sadly only three nights in a 4 bunk female room. And while the quarters were small, and beds somewhat rickety, WE HAD SUCH FUN HERE! We met so many wonderful travelers in their lounge, and spent long nights playing guitar and socializing with new friends. Very helpful and kind staff, and in PERFECT location if you enjoy the Montmartre district of Paris (which you should because its the best.) Easy to access the Metro as well, so you can get wherever you need to go! Highly recommend to young travelers, though may steer older generations away, simply for it's sleeping conditions. I'd totally stay here again!

Such a great discovery in Paris. Amazing location and views to the Sacre Coeur, great relation price-quality, clean and really nice staff. I went in a solo trip and the friendly but chill atmosphere of this hostel were exactly what I was looking for. Will definetely come back

Very nice hostel! Well located, clean, good staff and assistance. Your are at just one block far from Anvers subway station. Lots of restaurants, stores and markets in the block. Good atmosphere and courteous staff.

Great neighborhoid. Fantastic deck with spectacular view. Good common areas for socialisation. Nice sized rooms. I stayed in a 4 person en-suite. Beds were comfy. Room had a view of the Sacre Couer but black out curtains and nice mattress made afternoon nap possible. Breakfast was a good value if you had time.

The hostel is in a good location with nice restaurants and cafes close by, the staff were also really friendly and helpful. However the bedroom was absolutely freezing and there is a bar next to the hostel which plays music extremely loudly until the early hours of the morning making it very difficult to sleep.

The hostel was clean and was fine for a short stay. The staff were helpful and recommended a few local cafes go try. I didn't check out the bar, as I didn't realise it was in the building next door.

It's a small hostel with a basic kitchen and no social common room area. It has a lift that works. The breakfast wasn't great, €4 for cornflakes and pastries. At other hostels they provided cereal, yoghurt, scrambled eggs, bread and fruit. I'd save your money and go to the supermarket across the road or a cafe.

The hostel is situated in Montmarte, near the famous church on the hill. There are lots of cafes, pharmacies (every second shop in Paris seems to be a chemist) and the Moulin Rouge and Pigalle area is a short walk.

The hostel is on a bit of a dodgy, dirty street. I got off at Gard Du Nord straight from the airport. I was by myself during the middle of the day and felt a bit intimidated as it was crowded with men (unemployed and hanging out on the streets) from Africa and the Middle East talking to me in French and handing out flyers. There were over flowing rubbish bins, litter and pee in the streets. Not the Paris I had imagined...I would say this is a rough area of Paris, but further up near the church it's fine.
